Name: sprsSysUp
Description: Indicates that the sprs system is up and active.

Name: sprsSysDown
Description: Indicates that the sprs system is down.

Name: sprsUnableToAllocatePDPCtxtMemory
Description: Indicates PDP context memory is full.

Name: sprsIMSIMapRescan
Description: Indicates that the rescan of Sprs IMSI Mapping cache has started/completed/failed.

Name: sprsSQLExecution
Description: Indicates that SQL statement execution take more time then the configured threshold value.

Name: sprsSessionsRejected
Description: Indicates that too many sessions rejected or rejection of sessions reduced.

Name: sprsSessionsFailed
Description: Indicates that too many sessions failed or failing of sessions reduced.

Name: sprsSessionsRequest
Description: Indicates that Requested Sessions is above high water mark or Requested Sessions is reduced below low water mark.

Name: sprsGTPMsgQueueThreshold
Description: Indicates that the GTP Message Queue is goes above the threshold, goes below the threshold or goes to full capacity.

Name: sprsStrHomeProfileDNSReqFailed
Description: Indicates that too many Home Profile DNS Request Failed or failing of Home Profile DNS Request reduced.

Name: sprsStrLocalProfileDNSReqFailed
Description: Indicates that too many Local Profile DNS Request Failed or failing of Local Profile DNS Request reduced.

Name: dnsQueryAckErrorAlarm
Description: Indicates that too many DNS Query error received or receiving of DNS Query error reduced.

Name: dnsQueryAckTimeoutAlarm
Description: Indicates that too many DNS Query timeout received or receiving of DNS Query timeout reduced.
